# Testing Conventions

## Test Frameworks

| Layer | Framework | Location |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Domain / Unit | NUnit + FluentAssertions | `Siteswaps.Test/` |
| Generator / Arch | NUnit + ArchUnitNET + Verify | `Generator/Siteswaps.Generator.Test/` |
| MCP Server | NUnit | `Siteswaps.Mcp.Server.Test/` |
| E2E | Playwright + Reqnroll (xUnit) | `Siteswaps.E2ETests/` |
| Benchmarks | BenchmarkDotNet | `Generator/Siteswaps.Generator.Benchmarks/` |

## Patterns

- Use `[Test]` and `[TestCase(...)]` attributes (NUnit style)
- Assert with **FluentAssertions** (`value.Should().Be(...)`)
- Use **Verify** for snapshot testing — approved snapshots are committed to the repo
- Use **Meziantou InlineSnapshotTesting** for inline snapshot assertions
- E2E tests use **Page Object** pattern in `Siteswaps.E2ETests/`
- The E2E test server (`Siteswaps.E2ETests.Server`) hosts the Blazor WASM app for Playwright

## Architecture Tests

- `ArchitectureTests.cs` enforces layer boundaries using ArchUnitNET
- Generator core must not depend on UI components

## Running Tests

```bash
dotnet test              # run all tests
dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~SiteswapTest"  # run specific tests
```
